<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3734502>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Copulatory organs of Phrurolithus azarkinae sp. n. A–C male palp, prolateral, ventral and retrolateral; D epigyne intact, ventral; E macerated epigyne, dorsal; F dissected epigyne, ventral. Scale=0.2 mm. Abbreviations: Co—copulatory opening, Em—embolus, Fd—fertilization duct, Fe—femoral extension, Gr—receptacular gland, Pr—primary receptacle, Ra—retrolateral apophysis, Sd—sperm duct, Sr—secondary receptacle, Va—retroventral apophysis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3734502/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3734504>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. SEM micrographs of Phrurolithus azarkinae sp. n. (A–D) and Bosselaerius hyrcanicus sp. n. (E). A–C male palp, ventral, ventro-retrolateral and retrolateral; D terminal part of the male palp, ventral; E leg I, prolateral. Scale=0.1 mm. Abbreviations: Em—embolus, Pa—proventral apophysis, Ra—retrolateral apophysis, Sa—subterminal apophysis, Ta—terminal apophysis, Va—retroventral apophysis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3734504/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

